        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(gateway): wire coding tools into /tools/invoke HTTP surface",
        "body": "Builds on #85664. Narrow extension of the broader direct-invoke umbrella tracked in #37131.\n\n## Summary\n\nExtends PR #85664's narrow read-only landing to also expose `write` and `edit` via the gateway direct-invoke surfaces (HTTP `POST /tools/invoke` AND SDK RPC `tools.invoke`, which share the resolver). Same dual-key gating shape as #85664 — distinct surface-specific opt-in flag PLUS per-tool name in `gateway.tools.allow` — so existing configs that already list `\"write\"` or `\"edit\"` in `allow` for unrelated surfaces (e.g. an MCP/agent surface) stay inert at the direct-invoke layer.\n\n## Changes at current head `d1dc63e5b4`\n\nTwo additional fixes on top of prior head (`128f8f0fdc`):\n\n**[P1] Source-aware audit suppression (`audit-gateway-config.ts`):**\nOld code used a static `DUAL_KEY_GATED_TOOLS` set to suppress `dangerous_allow` for `read`/`write`/`edit` — even when the class opt-in was NOT set. A config with only `allow: [\"write\"]` (no `hostFsWrite: true`) would silently skip `dangerous_allow`, leaving no audit signal that a same-named plugin could be reachable. Fixed: suppression is now dynamic — only suppresses when the class opt-in IS active.\n\n**[P1] Plugin name collision (`tool-resolution.ts`):**\nOld code put `allTools` (plugins) before `codingTools`. A plugin named `read` would shadow the built-in filesystem tool even when `hostFsRead: true` was set. Fixed: coding built-ins now win name collision when the class opt-in is active.\n\n## Dual-key gating\n\nTo enable write-class tools on the direct-invoke surface, operators must set BOTH:\n\n| Key | Purpose | Default |\n|---|---|---|\n| `gateway.tools.directInvoke.hostFsWrite: true` | Class-level opt-in for the whole write family. | `false` |\n| `gateway.tools.allow: [...]` | Per-tool names to enable. | not present |\n\nTruth table (per tool name `T` ∈ `{write, edit}`):\n\n| `tools.allow` includes `T` | `directInvoke.hostFsWrite` | `T` reachable |\n|---|---|---|\n| no  | no   | ❌ |\n| yes | no   | ❌ (built-in not materialized; `dangerous_allow` audit fires) |\n| no  | yes  | ❌ (filtered by HTTP deny) |\n| yes | yes  | ✅ |\n\n## Scope\n\n- **Adds:** `write`, `edit` to direct-invoke (via `hostFsWrite: true` opt-in).\n- **Inherits from #85664:** `read` via `hostFsRead: true` opt-in.\n- **`apply_patch`:** in `DEFAULT_GATEWAY_HTTP_TOOL_DENY` for future-proofing; NOT produced by factory yet — deferred.\n- **NOT exposed:** `exec`, `process`, `spawn`, `shell` — RCE-class, requires separate owner/admin enforcement model.\n\n## Files changed\n\n- `src/config/types.gateway.ts` — adds `hostFsWrite?: boolean` to `GatewayDirectInvokeOptIns`\n- `src/security/dangerous-tools.ts` — adds `\"write\"`, `\"edit\"` to `DEFAULT_GATEWAY_HTTP_TOOL_DENY`\n- `src/gateway/tool-resolution.ts` — write/edit materialization; coding built-ins win name collision\n- `src/security/audit-gateway-config.ts` — `host_write_allow` finding; source-aware `dangerous_allow` suppression\n- `src/security/audit-gateway-tools-http.test.ts` — 19 test cases covering all gate combinations\n- `docs/gateway/tools-invoke-http-api.md` — dual-key opt-in docs + truth tables + audit behavior + plugin collision notes\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n> **Note (head `faf3ef3ca9`):** The live proof below ran at `d1dc63e5b4`. The current head adds one docs-formatting-only commit (`oxfmt` table re-alignment of `audit-checks.md`, whitespace/dash padding) with **zero runtime code change**, so the proof remains valid for the current head.\n\n**Behavior addressed:** Extend #85664's narrow read-only landing to also expose `write` and `edit` over Gateway direct-invoke surfaces, using the same dual-key gating pattern. Fixes source-aware audit suppression ([P1]) and coding built-in name collision precedence ([P1]).\n\n**Exact steps or command run after the patch:** `git checkout d1dc63e5b4 && docker run --name oc-63919-proof -v $PWD:/work -v oc_proof_nm:/work/node_modules --platform linux/arm64 -e NODE_OPTIONS=--max-old-space-size=12288 node:22-bookworm-slim bash /work/.build-and-proof-63919.sh` — exit 0.\n\n**Real environment tested:** built fresh from head `d1dc63e5b4662b87528a76ba72c3b5d0d5a94993` inside `node:22-bookworm-slim` arm64-native container (pnpm v11.2.2, linux-arm64 packages in named volume). Gateway started per case via `openclaw gateway run`; each case dispatched via HTTP `POST /tools/invoke` AND SDK `GatewayClientTransport` WebSocket `oc.tools.invoke(...)`.\nUnit tests (Docker, linux/arm64): 124 total — 19/19 (audit-gateway-tools-http) + 105/105 (tools-invoke-http). Full build + SDK build: all phases completed.\n\n**Evidence after fix:** live terminal output from `docker run node:22-bookworm-slim` at head `d1dc63e5b4`:\n\n```\n=== HEAD: d1dc63e5b4662b87528a76ba72c3b5d0d5a94993 ===\n\n### TESTS (audit-gateway-tools-http) ###\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\nTests       19 passed (19)\n\n### TESTS (tools-invoke-http) ###\nTest Files  3 passed (3)\nTests       105 passed (105)\n\n### BUILD ###\n[build-all] plugins:assets:build done in 449ms\n[build-all] tsdown done in 167.7s\n[build-all] build:plugin-sdk:dts done in 8.66s\n[build-all] ui:build done in 870ms\nBUILD OK\n\n### SDK BUILD ###\ndist/index.mjs  30.52 kB\nSDK BUILD OK\n\n### LIVE PROOF ###\n\n--- R-DENIED (allow:[\"read\"], hfsR=false) ---\n  [HTTP] 404 {\"ok\":false,\"error\":{\"type\":\"not_found\",\"message\":\"Tool not available: read\"}}\n  [SDK]  ok=false not_found\n\n--- R-ENABLED (allow:[\"read\"], hfsR=true) ---\n  [HTTP] 200 {\"ok\":true,\"result\":{\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"PROOF READ SOURCE at d1dc63e5b4...\\n\"}]}}\n  [SDK]  ok=true source=core, same content\n\n--- W-DENIED (allow:[\"write\"], hfsW=false) ---\n  [HTTP] 404 {\"ok\":false,\"error\":{\"type\":\"not_found\",\"message\":\"Tool not available: write\"}}\n  [SDK]  ok=false not_found\n\n--- W-ENABLED (allow:[\"write\",\"edit\"], hfsW=true) ---\n  [HTTP] 200 {\"ok\":true,\"result\":{\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Successfully wrote 52 bytes to /tmp/proof-write-63919.txt\"}]}}\n  [SDK]  ok=true source=core, same result\n\n--- E-DENIED (allow:[\"edit\"], hfsW=false) ---\n  [HTTP] 404 {\"ok\":false,\"error\":{\"type\":\"not_found\",\"message\":\"Tool not available: edit\"}}\n  [SDK]  ok=false not_found\n\n--- E-ENABLED (allow:[\"edit\",\"write\"], hfsW=true) ---\n  [HTTP] 200 {\"ok\":true,\"result\":{\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Successfully replaced 1 block(s) in /tmp/proof-edit-63919.txt.\"}],...}}\n  [SDK]  ok=true source=core, same result\n\n--- RCE (allow:[\"exec\"], hfsR=true, hfsW=true) ---\n  [HTTP] 404 {\"ok\":false,\"error\":{\"type\":\"not_found\",\"message\":\"Tool not available: exec\"}}\n  [SDK]  ok=false not_found\n\n=== FINAL FILE STATES ===\n[read-source]: PROOF READ SOURCE at d1dc63e5b4662b87528a76ba72c3b5d0d5a94993\n[write-target]: PROOF WRITE d1dc63e5b4662b87528a76ba72c3b5d0d5a94993\n[edit-target]: EDITED at d1dc63e5b4662b87528a76ba72c3b5d0d5a94993\n\n=== PROOF COMPLETE: HEAD=d1dc63e5b4662b87528a76ba72c3b5d0d5a94993 ===\n```\n\n**Observed result after fix:** All 7 direct-invoke cases confirmed. Gated tools (`write`, `edit`) only reachable when BOTH `directInvoke.hostFsWrite: true` AND `gateway.tools.allow` includes the tool name — confirmed via HTTP `POST /tools/invoke` (200) and SDK `tools.invoke` (ok=true). RCE-class `exec` returns 404 regardless of flags.\n\n**Not tested:** `apply_patch` (in deny list, not yet factory-produced); `exec`/`process`/`shell` (RCE-class, require separate owner/admin enforcement model, deferred).\n\n**Per-surface matrix (head `d1dc63e5b4`):**\n\n| Case | Gating | HTTP `/tools/invoke` | SDK `tools.invoke` |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| read denied (only `allow`) | unreachable | ✅ 404 not_found | ✅ ok=false not_found |\n| read enabled (both keys) | reachable | ✅ 200 + file contents | ✅ ok=true + file contents |\n| write denied (only `allow`) | unreachable | ✅ 404 not_found | ✅ ok=false not_found |\n| write enabled (both keys) | reachable | ✅ 200 + 52 bytes written | ✅ ok=true + 52 bytes written |\n| edit denied (only `allow`) | unreachable | ✅ 404 not_found | ✅ ok=false not_found |\n| edit enabled (both keys) | reachable | ✅ 200 + \"replaced 1 block(s)\" | ✅ ok=true + \"replaced 1 block(s)\" |\n| RCE attempt (`exec`, all flags) | structurally unreachable | ✅ 404 not_found | ✅ ok=false not_found |\n\n",
        "branch": "feat/tools-invoke-coding-tools-upstream",
